cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the decidability of the entailment problem in Separation Logic with inductive definitions, which is a topic related to logic and programming languages (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of tree automata also suggests a connection to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), while the complexity analysis and implementation aspects are relevant to computational complexity (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL).
